AidTypeVocabulary

Source: R/data.R
AidTypeVocabulary.Rd

The AidTypeVocabulary codelist defines a range of external codelists which themselves provide codes and descriptions for aid type. This is a Non-Core codelist.

AidTypeVocabulary

Format

A data frame with 4 rows and 6 variables:

code

double COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

name

character COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

description

character COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

category

logical COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

url

character COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

status

character COLUMN_DESCRIPTION

Source

https://iatistandard.org/en/iati-standard/203/codelists/

Examples

{
head(AidTypeVocabulary,10)
}

#> # A tibble: 4 x 6
